WEBVTT

00:04.080 --> 00:05.069
[Calvin]
Previously on Siren.

00:05.080 --> 00:06.661
[Beth] Members
of the group rarely leave.

00:06.670 --> 00:08.114
When they do, people remember.

00:08.120 --> 00:10.998
What happened to your folks
wasn't right.

00:11.000 --> 00:12.661
I'll never forget it.

00:12.670 --> 00:14.820
[Ted] You were asking
about the well.

00:14.830 --> 00:17.537
There used to be
a cottage next to It,
am I right?

00:17.540 --> 00:18.575
That's right.
How 'd you know that?

00:18.580 --> 00:20.207
[movie projector running]

00:20.210 --> 00:21.666
For you.

00:21.670 --> 00:23.160
So you remember me.

00:23.170 --> 00:24.660
[Ryn]
Others in danger.

00:24.670 --> 00:26.160
He save them,

00:26.170 --> 00:27.239
but he die.

00:27.250 --> 00:28.877
Can we just--
just fact check?

00:28.880 --> 00:30.666
So the three of you

00:30.670 --> 00:32.615
are working
with the military

00:32.620 --> 00:35.783
to get some genetic goo
out of Ryn,

00:35.790 --> 00:37.701
and because of all of this,

00:37.710 --> 00:39.496
-Ryn just went beast mode...
-[screams]

00:39.500 --> 00:41.536
...and how about the fact that
Ryn just did her thing to you,

00:41.540 --> 00:42.666
and you're acting
like it's nothing?

00:42.670 --> 00:44.456
[Ryn] Maddie is not okay.

00:44.460 --> 00:45.950
I mean, I'm sorry,

00:45.960 --> 00:47.370
but y'all need to get
your damn heads checked!

00:47.380 --> 00:48.608
[screams]

00:49.830 --> 00:53.459
[ticking clock echoing]

00:56.460 --> 00:57.916
[scraping]

00:57.920 --> 00:59.911
[ticking]

00:59.920 --> 01:01.035
[Nicole, voice echoing]
Maddie?

01:03.830 --> 01:04.876
Maddie?

01:06.500 --> 01:07.615
Maddie?

01:09.790 --> 01:10.779
You okay?

01:12.580 --> 01:15.208
Sorry.
What was the question?

01:15.210 --> 01:17.030
Have you ever suffered
from delusions?

01:17.040 --> 01:18.166
Hallucinations?

01:18.170 --> 01:19.819
No, I haven't.

01:19.830 --> 01:21.491
I mean, not before this.

01:21.500 --> 01:22.876
Can I get some water?

01:22.880 --> 01:24.825
Yeah, of course.

01:27.750 --> 01:29.240
[door opens]

01:30.250 --> 01:31.615
How much longer?

01:33.460 --> 01:34.575
I'm not sure.

01:34.580 --> 01:35.956
I'll try to speed it along.

01:38.830 --> 01:40.878
Why they keep Maddie
there so long?

01:40.880 --> 01:42.780
Asking questions.

01:42.790 --> 01:45.452
They're trying to understand
what's going on inside her head.

01:45.460 --> 01:48.418
It's_ca|led _
a psychological evaluation.

01:51.920 --> 01:53.820
I see you're an only child.

01:53.830 --> 01:55.457
Raised mostly
by your stepfather.

01:57.120 --> 01:59.702
Your mother wasn't _
always your primary caregiver.

01:59.710 --> 02:01.996
It says here she attended

02:02.000 --> 02:04.992
-inpatient substance abuse
_ rehabilitation...
-[ticking grows louder]

02:05.000 --> 02:06.740
three separate times.

02:06.750 --> 02:09.287
[voice echoing] Do you think
those circumstances

02:09.290 --> 02:11.918
could've contributed
to your current difficulties?

02:11.920 --> 02:13.785
Excuse me?

02:13.790 --> 02:16.918
[normal sound] Often,
a child raised in a home

02:16.920 --> 02:18.569
with a history
of substance abuse

02:18.580 --> 02:20.411
displays a lack
of impulsivity control--

02:20.420 --> 02:22.320
Stop!

02:22.330 --> 02:24.742
You have no idea who I am
or what I've been through.

02:24.750 --> 02:26.786
Maddie, she just wants
to get the full picture

02:26.790 --> 02:29.532
of what this all means,
where your reactions stem from.

02:29.540 --> 02:31.747
You're not being
attacked here.

02:31.750 --> 02:33.536
You don't know me.

02:34.960 --> 02:36.666
You know what?
Screw this.

02:36.670 --> 02:37.955
Let me out of here.

02:37.960 --> 02:40.372
Maddie, please.
Let us help you.

02:40.380 --> 02:41.779
I want out!

02:48.620 --> 02:50.167
-Maddie--
-Don't.

02:54.420 --> 02:56.411
Maddie's not okay.

02:56.420 --> 02:58.536
You go through this, too?

02:58.540 --> 02:59.529
In your head?

02:59.540 --> 03:01.952
In a different way, yeah.

03:01.960 --> 03:03.575
Same feeling, though.

03:03.580 --> 03:04.786
Out of control.

03:09.540 --> 03:11.246
I help Ben and Maddie.

03:26.580 --> 03:27.990
[bones crunching]

03:28.000 --> 03:29.820
[screaming]

03:32.670 --> 03:35.742
[high-pitched call]

03:42.880 --> 03:45.371
I tried searching online,

03:45.380 --> 03:48.998
but the paper's
digital archives
only went back so far.

03:49.000 --> 03:52.208
Is this is everything
from 1962?

03:52.210 --> 03:53.825
Yeah, anything
that predates the web

03:53.830 --> 03:54.990
will be found on this floor.

03:55.000 --> 03:56.490
Oh. Myself included.

03:56.500 --> 03:57.956
[laughs] Thanks.

03:57.960 --> 03:59.279
No worries.

04:10.460 --> 04:13.372
[mysterious music]

04:36.040 --> 04:37.996
[gasping]

04:41.250 --> 04:42.285
[Ben] How are you feeling?

04:42.290 --> 04:44.110
Myself again.

04:45.540 --> 04:47.201
It's like something
triggers me.

04:47.210 --> 04:50.282
I act out, and afterwards,
I'm aware of what I did,

04:50.290 --> 04:52.030
I just don't know
why I did it.

04:52.040 --> 04:53.246
I know what you mean.

04:53.250 --> 04:55.070
It's like another side
of you takes over.

04:55.080 --> 04:58.618
I'm sorry about what happened
at your parents' house.

04:58.620 --> 05:00.827
It's okay.

05:00.830 --> 05:03.537
That night, I thought
I saw Ryn on the road,

05:03.540 --> 05:05.417
but she wasn't there.

05:05.420 --> 05:08.207
And maybe there's
no fixing it-- the song.

05:08.210 --> 05:09.916
I mean,
what if this is it?

05:09.920 --> 05:10.955
Our new normal.

05:10.960 --> 05:12.609
We're gonna figure it out.

05:12.620 --> 05:14.030
We're gonna be all right

05:17.580 --> 05:18.615
Ryn.

05:18.620 --> 05:20.451
She is healer.

05:20.460 --> 05:21.825
She will help us.

05:22.880 --> 05:24.871
[shooting sound effects]

05:27.210 --> 05:29.576
-[Xander] Gotcha.
-[Nicole] This is too easy.

05:31.170 --> 05:32.205
Yaah!

05:32.210 --> 05:33.996
[Xander growls]

05:34.000 --> 05:36.207
Okay, fine, fine, fine.
All right.

05:36.210 --> 05:38.371
No pictures, please.

05:38.380 --> 05:40.996
Easy, easy, easy.
If that was Whack-a-Mole,

05:41.000 --> 05:42.536
I would have just
swept the floor with you.

05:42.540 --> 05:45.031
Okay. Whatever helps you
sleep at night, McClure.

05:45.040 --> 05:47.417
For the record, I was
more into Nintendo as a kid.

05:47.420 --> 05:48.956
You know, like
Super Mario Brothers,

05:48.960 --> 05:50.996
Donkey Kong,
Legends of Zelda.

05:51.000 --> 05:51.955
Sonic the Hedgehog.

05:51.960 --> 05:54.167
Okay, that was Sega,
not Nintendo.

05:54.170 --> 05:56.707
You're failing me, Martinez.
You're failing me.

05:56.710 --> 05:59.873
Well, it sounds like you had
a very active social life.

05:59.880 --> 06:01.029
Oh, you have no idea.

06:03.120 --> 06:04.997
My dad never let me
play video games.

06:05.000 --> 06:07.958
He thought they
"reduced academic achievement."

06:07.960 --> 06:09.746
Those were his words,
not mine.

06:09.750 --> 06:11.240
Okay, then how'd
you get so good then?

06:11.250 --> 06:12.490
Played them anyway.

06:15.080 --> 06:16.160
This feels good.

06:16.170 --> 06:17.455
What?

06:17.460 --> 06:20.076
This. You and me.

06:21.250 --> 06:24.037
It almost feels... normal.

06:25.460 --> 06:26.700
I know what you mean.

06:28.170 --> 06:29.706
I propose a toast.

06:29.710 --> 06:31.029
Hmm.

06:31.040 --> 06:32.871
To, um...

06:32.880 --> 06:36.168
To this, right here.

06:36.170 --> 06:37.535
To leaving all that crap
in the past.

06:37.540 --> 06:40.748
And, um, to honesty.

06:40.750 --> 06:42.706
To honesty.

06:47.380 --> 06:48.995
[Helen]
Did you know about this?

06:49.000 --> 06:50.570
Did you know it was arson?

06:50.580 --> 06:52.116
Don't you think
I would've mentioned it?

06:52.120 --> 06:54.372
This is all way
before my time, Helen.

06:54.380 --> 06:56.996
Well, did your father ever
say anything to you?

06:57.000 --> 06:59.958
You know as well as I do,
my father was never
a big sharer.

06:59.960 --> 07:02.110
Well, according to this,

07:02.120 --> 07:04.998
my parents were staying
in your family's cottage
the night of the fire.

07:05.000 --> 07:07.286
Why would your family
have been staying
in our cottage?

07:07.290 --> 07:09.372
Your guess
is as good as mine.

07:09.380 --> 07:11.075
But_this article
says it was arson,

07:11.080 --> 07:13.207
which means
my father was murdered.

07:13.210 --> 07:15.030
Are you suggesting my family
had something to do with that?

07:15.040 --> 07:16.826
I'm just stating the facts.

07:18.540 --> 07:19.950
[sighs]

07:22.080 --> 07:23.069
I'm sorry.

07:24.330 --> 07:25.957
"No suspects were identified.

07:25.960 --> 07:27.871
Motivation for the crime
remains unclear."

07:27.880 --> 07:29.609
Look, I'm sure that there is

07:29.620 --> 07:31.827
a perfectly logical
explanation for all this.

07:34.880 --> 07:38.702
[mysterious music]

07:51.250 --> 07:52.069
Hands.

07:52.080 --> 07:53.911
Do what she says.

07:56.170 --> 07:57.706
[shells clacking]

08:05.790 --> 08:08.418
[single mermaid's song
echoing]

08:18.960 --> 08:20.166
[shells clacking]

08:29.040 --> 08:31.952
[chorus of mermaid voices
echoing]

08:31.960 --> 08:33.166
[gaSPSI

08:35.170 --> 08:36.319
Can you help them?

08:36.330 --> 08:37.410
No.

08:37.420 --> 08:38.819
Too strong.

08:39.830 --> 08:40.819
In head.

08:50.170 --> 08:51.239
You know how.

08:52.250 --> 08:53.239
Tell me.

08:54.620 --> 08:57.498
Humans help us
get back in water.

08:57.500 --> 08:59.240
Now we must help humans.

08:59.250 --> 09:01.992
The song,
it hurt Ben and Maddie.

09:02.000 --> 09:04.537
Tell me how to help them.

09:04.540 --> 09:09.375
There is place
where sound heals.

09:09.380 --> 09:12.747
Ryn, what's
she talking about?

09:12.750 --> 09:16.493
There is place.
In the ocean.

09:16.500 --> 09:19.162
Secret place
where sound is kept.

09:20.580 --> 09:23.413
My mother tell me about it
when I was young.

09:23.420 --> 09:24.819
Have you been there?

09:24.830 --> 09:29.164
No. Only healers go.

09:29.170 --> 09:31.411
I tell you where.

09:34.330 --> 09:35.376
Humans cannot go.

09:36.790 --> 09:38.246
Too deep in water.

09:38.250 --> 09:40.286
[dramatic music]

09:45.290 --> 09:47.827
[Kyle] Okay, let me
get this straight.

09:47.830 --> 09:51.823
You want to use
the Naw's resources
to investigate this, um...

09:51.830 --> 09:52.910
What'd you say it was?

09:52.920 --> 09:54.956
An oceanic sound source.

09:54.960 --> 09:56.575
From what Ryn told us,

09:56.580 --> 09:58.707
it seems to be some kind
of underwater echo chamber.

09:58.710 --> 10:00.109
And she believes going down
to this chamber

10:00.120 --> 10:02.168
might help
with the effects of this song?

10:02.170 --> 10:03.910
If we can get there, yes.

10:03.920 --> 10:06.377
You know
how far-fetched this sounds?

10:06.380 --> 10:07.824
[Ben] A few months ago,
I would've said

10:07.830 --> 10:09.286
the same thing
about mermaids.

10:09.290 --> 10:10.416
[scoffs]

10:12.000 --> 10:16.289
You know, when I was deployed
in Kuwait back in '91,

10:16.290 --> 10:19.373
my unit's motto was
"in God we trust.

10:20.790 --> 10:22.371
All others we monitor."

10:22.380 --> 10:24.416
Meaning what exactly?

10:24.420 --> 10:25.876
You're a civilian,
asking me to lend you

10:25.880 --> 10:28.610
multi-million_ dollar
research eqUIpment.

10:28.620 --> 10:30.451
Why should I put
my trust in you?

10:30.460 --> 10:33.327
Funny. I asked myself
the same thing about--

10:33.330 --> 10:34.786
It could be an opportunity

10:34.790 --> 10:36.371
to shed some more light
on the song, sir.

10:41.420 --> 10:44.241
Okay, but you're in charge.

10:44.250 --> 10:45.569
Yes, sir.

10:45.580 --> 10:47.070
Anything they see down there,
I want to see, too.

10:47.080 --> 10:48.911
-You understand me?
-Copy.

10:48.920 --> 10:52.287
And I want
this entire expedition
fully documented.

10:52.290 --> 10:53.370
[Nicole] Yes, sir.

10:59.330 --> 11:00.570
There.

11:00.580 --> 11:02.241
You see that?

11:02.250 --> 11:03.456
Wait.

11:05.170 --> 11:06.990
It looks like a person.

11:07.000 --> 11:10.072
A person in a place
impossible to reach
without gear.

11:10.080 --> 11:12.913
That's why they're sweeping
this whole eco-terror attack
under the rug.

11:12.920 --> 11:13.989
Who is?

11:14.000 --> 11:15.956
The military, man.

11:15.960 --> 11:19.248
I've been working at Klesco
for almost five years.

11:19.250 --> 11:20.706
Last year, they put
away a tree hugger

11:20.710 --> 11:22.917
just for taggin' a ship
with a peace sign.

11:22.920 --> 11:24.740
They don't just let things go.

11:24.750 --> 11:27.287
So you're telling me
the United States
military stepped in

11:29.170 --> 11:31.035
That's what I'm saying.

11:31.040 --> 11:32.280
Days after the attack,

11:32.290 --> 11:34.611
Feds came in
and swiped all the footage.

11:37.330 --> 11:39.036
Not all the footage.

11:40.830 --> 11:42.161
[door opens]

11:43.960 --> 11:45.825
[rock music
playing in The Anchor]

11:48.000 --> 11:49.285
That one still has
lipstick on it.

11:49.290 --> 11:51.611
Oh, yeah.
See, that's, um--

11:51.620 --> 11:53.451
That's actually my glass.

11:53.460 --> 11:54.745
I just haven't finished
drinking from it yet.

11:54.750 --> 11:56.456
Not really your shade.

11:56.460 --> 11:58.746
Really? Mm, I don't know.

11:59.750 --> 12:01.320
Um, are you hungry?

12:01.330 --> 12:02.570
We got a new Cajun
quesadilla on the menu.

12:02.580 --> 12:03.820
I can fire up the grill.

12:05.420 --> 12:07.661
Xanden
I owe you an apology.

12:07.670 --> 12:11.458
What I did was
completely out of line.

12:11.460 --> 12:12.745
I was messed up.

12:12.750 --> 12:14.615
Because of the song, right?

12:14.620 --> 12:17.919
It lowered my inhibitions,
these old feelings came up,

12:17.920 --> 12:20.912
and you got caught
in the crossfire, Xan.

12:20.920 --> 12:21.909
I'm sorry.

12:21.920 --> 12:23.035
"Old feelings."

12:23.040 --> 12:25.611
I wasn't myself.

12:27.620 --> 12:29.668
Yeah. I figured as much.

12:29.670 --> 12:30.955
_ It's been awhile _
Since you pounded a pitcher

12:30.960 --> 12:32.700
like a frat boy
on pledge week.

12:35.620 --> 12:39.704
But, um, I mean,
you're okay now, yeah?

12:39.710 --> 12:40.995
Getting there.

12:41.000 --> 12:44.458
Look, um, so your mom

12:45.460 --> 12:47.030
stopped by to see me.

12:48.040 --> 12:50.531
And she says that

12:52.500 --> 12:55.742
you're in a relationship
with Ben and Ryn.

12:58.040 --> 12:59.576
Why would she
tell you that?

12:59.580 --> 13:01.320
She's worried about you.

13:01.330 --> 13:03.070
So am I.

13:03.080 --> 13:06.868
I mean, are you sure
that this thing
that's in your head,

13:06.880 --> 13:09.872
it's not making you
think that you have
feelings for Ryn?

13:09.880 --> 13:11.950
I mean, what if that's
not real either?

13:11.960 --> 13:13.530
I mean, you have
no idea what this thing
could be doing to you.

13:13.540 --> 13:15.952
I had feelings for her
before it happened.

13:15.960 --> 13:19.327
You know, you don't always need
to worry about me, Xander.

13:19.330 --> 13:20.957
I can take care of myself.

13:23.750 --> 13:24.990
I'm sorry.

13:27.790 --> 13:28.825
I'm sorry.

13:38.710 --> 13:39.699
What is it?

13:39.710 --> 13:41.416
We find more--

13:42.460 --> 13:44.496
male, female.

13:44.500 --> 13:46.070
But no young.

13:51.420 --> 13:53.160
We will make more babies.

13:53.170 --> 13:54.489
When tides change.

14:06.080 --> 14:07.536
Safe to show humans place?

14:07.540 --> 14:11.988
Yes. It is safe
with Ben and Maddie.

14:12.000 --> 14:14.992
It's capable of reaching
depths of 4,000 meters.

14:15.000 --> 14:16.319
[Ben]
The sub in Washington

14:16.330 --> 14:18.912
only went as deep
as 1,200 meters.

14:18.920 --> 14:21.206
[Maddie] You're moving on up
since your grad school days.

14:21.210 --> 14:22.495
[Ben] Apparently.

14:22.500 --> 14:23.819
What's its max speed?

14:23.830 --> 14:25.741
Goes up
to four and a half knots.

14:25.750 --> 14:28.116
Cameras are placed
on each beam.

14:28.120 --> 14:29.280
They'll be our eyes
from the ship,

14:29.290 --> 14:31.281
help us document
the whole journey.

14:31.290 --> 14:32.700
All right?

14:32.710 --> 14:33.916
Let's get you inside.

14:36.210 --> 14:38.496
This goes in water?

14:38.500 --> 14:39.615
With us inside?

14:39.620 --> 14:41.781
That's the idea.

15:00.290 --> 15:01.780
-Hey.
-Hey.

15:01.790 --> 15:04.031
Ooh! My break's
only ten minutes.

15:04.040 --> 15:06.281
Thanks for meeting me.

15:06.290 --> 15:08.110
So this is where you work?
It's cute.

15:08.120 --> 15:10.111
Yeah, it pays the bills.

15:10.120 --> 15:11.530
What do you wanna
talk to me about?

15:13.290 --> 15:14.496
Your friend, Helen.

15:14.500 --> 15:16.115
What about her?

15:16.120 --> 15:17.417
Don't take this
the wrong way,

15:17.420 --> 15:19.536
but how sure are you
she can be trusted

15:19.540 --> 15:21.167
with our secret?

15:21.170 --> 15:23.161
It's her secret, too, Beth.
She's one of us.

15:23.170 --> 15:25.286
She's known this
her entire life.

15:25.290 --> 15:27.918
She's very outspoken.

15:27.920 --> 15:30.491
We're not safe.
You know that, right?

15:30.500 --> 15:31.740
The more people
who know about us,

15:31.750 --> 15:33.206
the more danger
we're all in.

15:33.210 --> 15:34.495
She's not gonna
do that to us.

15:34.500 --> 15:35.910
How do you know that?

15:35.920 --> 15:38.536
-[sighs]
-[men outside conversing]

15:38.540 --> 15:39.529
What?

15:39.540 --> 15:41.326
[doors slam, engine starts]

15:41.330 --> 15:43.742
Riclq, is there something
you're not telling me?

15:47.120 --> 15:48.747
She can be trusted, okay?

15:48.750 --> 15:50.661
She kept their secret,

15:50.670 --> 15:52.114
and they're in danger, too.

15:52.120 --> 15:53.109
Who do you mean?

15:53.120 --> 15:55.111
Helen's made contact
with our kind.

15:56.670 --> 15:58.991
But full-blooded ones
from the ocean.

15:59.000 --> 16:00.376
And they were
in Bristol Cove.

16:00.380 --> 16:01.574
Don't joke with me.

16:01.580 --> 16:03.787
I'm not.
I've met them, Beth.

16:03.790 --> 16:06.418
As soon as I saw them,
I knew.

16:06.420 --> 16:09.071
You're telling me
they're in Bristol Cove?

16:09.080 --> 16:10.661
They're back
in the water now, but...

16:12.420 --> 16:14.877
believe me, they exist.

16:19.210 --> 16:23.283
[rock music playing
in The Anchor]

16:23.290 --> 16:25.167
C'mon, Xan, just
one more beer, all right?

16:25.170 --> 16:26.159
You know I'm good for it.

16:26.170 --> 16:27.876
Broken record, man.

16:27.880 --> 16:29.245
You ain't been good
for it for over a week.

16:29.250 --> 16:30.285
I told you to quit
that poker shit.

16:30.290 --> 16:31.609
You obviously suck at it.

16:31.620 --> 16:33.372
That's the name of the game,
sink or swim.

16:33.380 --> 16:36.998
Okay, so is this the sinking
or the swimming?

16:37.000 --> 16:39.377
I'll be back
on my feet in no time.

16:42.620 --> 16:44.201
All right, all right, fine.

16:46.120 --> 16:48.202
This is the last one,
all right?

16:48.210 --> 16:50.246
And don't tell Janine.
She's gonna dock
my pay again.

16:50.250 --> 16:52.707
I gotta help Mom
pay the bills this month.

16:52.710 --> 16:55.998
["Be Mine"
by Offenbach playing]

17:04.790 --> 17:06.530
You gotta be kiddin' me.

17:06.540 --> 17:08.280
And I want you to be mine

17:11.210 --> 17:13.201
Yeah, I want you to be mine

17:17.420 --> 17:19.786
["Be Mine"
by Offenbach playing]

17:19.790 --> 17:21.326
Hello.

17:21.330 --> 17:23.207
What the hell
are you doin' here?

17:23.210 --> 17:27.783
Levi come back to land.
Be human.

17:27.790 --> 17:29.576
You can't be here.

17:29.580 --> 17:31.116
Do you have any idea
what we went through

17:31.120 --> 17:32.109
to get you back
into the water?

17:32.120 --> 17:33.371
We nearly got killed.

17:33.380 --> 17:36.281
-His boat burned.
-Land is good for me.

17:36.290 --> 17:37.530
I don't care, man.

17:37.540 --> 17:38.996
You have no clue
how to survwe here.

17:39.000 --> 17:40.319
-You gotta go.
-No!

17:42.420 --> 17:44.320
Man, people are looking.

17:44.330 --> 17:47.458
Okay. Um, hey, hey, hey.
I'll tell you what.

17:47.460 --> 17:50.611
You come with me outside,

17:50.620 --> 17:52.372
and I'll, uh--

17:52.380 --> 17:54.200
I'll give you a free beer.

17:54.210 --> 17:55.746
Been

17:55.750 --> 17:57.456
Yeah.

18:04.290 --> 18:06.451
[Ben] Make sure to lower her
slowly from the helm.

18:06.460 --> 18:08.610
The waves are strong,
we'll feel the push.

18:08.620 --> 18:10.110
Ben,
I'm on channel 22.

18:10.120 --> 18:11.280
You'll be in my ear
the entire time.

18:11.290 --> 18:12.370
I'll give you the green light

18:12.380 --> 18:13.369
when we're set for descent.

18:13.380 --> 18:14.415
You ready?

18:14.420 --> 18:15.739
Is that
a rhetorical question?

18:18.170 --> 18:21.412
[suspenseful music]

18:25.460 --> 18:26.745
[crewman] All clear!

18:26.750 --> 18:28.160
[crewman 2]
Check the ballast.

18:29.540 --> 18:31.110
They will be watching.

18:32.290 --> 18:35.168
It'll be okay.
Trust me.

18:35.170 --> 18:36.285
Okay. Yes.

18:39.960 --> 18:41.279
We got this.

18:46.500 --> 18:47.706
Good luck.

19:02.960 --> 19:04.370
[Ben, on radio]
Nautac One.

19:04.380 --> 19:05.779
Nautac One
to research bridge.

19:05.790 --> 19:07.075
Prepare to launch.

19:07.080 --> 19:08.570
Research bridge
to Nautac One.

19:08.580 --> 19:10.241
Final systems check. Over.

19:10.250 --> 19:14.118
External pressure 14.7 psi.

19:14.120 --> 19:16.452
Surface temperature
52 degrees Fahrenheit.

19:16.460 --> 19:18.030
Ready to descend.

19:19.120 --> 19:19.950
[Nicole] Roger that.

19:22.080 --> 19:24.116
Roger that.

19:30.290 --> 19:33.248
[electric motors whirring]

19:38.960 --> 19:43.579
[placid music]

19:46.380 --> 19:49.167
Must be strange,
seeing the ocean like this.

19:49.170 --> 19:50.114
With human eyes.

19:50.120 --> 19:51.200
Yes.

19:51.210 --> 19:52.825
What do you think?

19:52.830 --> 19:55.458
Home is beautiful.

20:13.250 --> 20:14.820
[Nicole] Research bridge
to Nautac One.

20:14.830 --> 20:16.036
What's your depth? Over.

20:18.750 --> 20:20.911
Nautac One
to research bridge,

20:20.920 --> 20:22.114
60 meters.

20:23.670 --> 20:25.160
[Nicole] Copy that.

20:34.330 --> 20:36.992
[female singer on radio]
I've heard people whisper

20:37.000 --> 20:38.536
[knock on door]

20:38.540 --> 20:41.953
That you
aren't being true

20:41.960 --> 20:43.746
I'm sorry
for the intrusion.

20:43.750 --> 20:46.742
You probably
don't even remember me.

20:46.750 --> 20:49.913
Helen. Did anybody
see you come in here?

20:49.920 --> 20:51.740
-Nobody.
-You're sure?

20:51.750 --> 20:53.069
Yes.

20:53.080 --> 20:55.958
You said
at the party

20:55.960 --> 20:57.871
what happened to my parents
wasn't right.

20:59.120 --> 21:00.326
What did you mean
by that?

21:02.250 --> 21:03.239
-[switches off radio]
-John.

21:04.330 --> 21:05.319
Please.

21:08.750 --> 21:12.038
I didn't know your father,
not personally.

21:12.040 --> 21:16.409
But your mother and I,
we had a close kinship.

21:16.420 --> 21:17.455
How close?

21:17.460 --> 21:19.416
We were set
to marry.

21:20.880 --> 21:22.245
It was an arranged marriage,

21:22.250 --> 21:24.992
a way to keep
the bloodline going.

21:26.210 --> 21:27.871
The wedding never happened.

21:30.040 --> 21:32.201
She was in love
With someone else.

21:33.580 --> 21:34.615
My father.

21:39.380 --> 21:40.995
What happened?

21:41.000 --> 21:44.072
Your father was human,
your mother one of us.

21:44.080 --> 21:46.457
It was forbidden.

21:46.460 --> 21:48.109
Caused an uproar.

21:48.120 --> 21:50.076
They called it
a betrayal.

21:50.080 --> 21:53.117
It got so bad,
your folks had
to go into hiding.

21:55.620 --> 21:56.871
Keep it.

21:56.880 --> 21:57.949
Thank you.

21:59.420 --> 22:01.285
Can I ask you
another question?

22:03.080 --> 22:06.163
Do you think
the group was capable
of murdering my father?

22:08.250 --> 22:10.571
They'd do anything
to protect the secret.

22:12.330 --> 22:13.410
Anything.

22:17.620 --> 22:19.201
Walk that way,

22:19.210 --> 22:22.031
and keep walking until
you can't walk anymore,

22:22.040 --> 22:24.031
and then you walk
right into the water.

22:25.830 --> 22:26.990
He's not walking.

22:28.210 --> 22:32.988
Dude, we don't want you here!

22:33.000 --> 22:34.319
I don't-- I don't know
how to make that any clearer.

22:34.330 --> 22:35.376
Just go!

22:50.460 --> 22:52.166
-[line rings]
-You've reached Ben Pownall.

22:52.170 --> 22:53.410
I'm not available.
Leave a message.

22:53.420 --> 22:55.240
Ben, where are you?

22:55.250 --> 22:56.319
Just call me back,
all right?

22:56.330 --> 22:58.070
This is bullshit.

22:58.080 --> 23:00.958
Hey, Cal, been tryin'
to get a hold of you.

23:00.960 --> 23:03.417
I'm gonna getting you
the money, I swear.

23:03.420 --> 23:04.535
Uh-huh.

23:06.170 --> 23:07.205
-[groans]
-Hey!

23:09.330 --> 23:11.537
_ -Aah!
[groans]

23:14.460 --> 23:16.109
[grunting]

23:17.500 --> 23:18.706
_ -AahI
[thug] okay.

23:18.710 --> 23:19.699
[both grunting]

23:20.710 --> 23:22.200
[groaning]

23:30.040 --> 23:32.998
Yeah, that's right!
You better run!

23:49.580 --> 23:51.116
[Ben, on radio]
Nautac One.

23:51.120 --> 23:52.701
Nautac One
to research bridge.

23:52.710 --> 23:54.280
We've reached the seafloor.

23:54.290 --> 23:56.281
Copy that.
What's your depth?

23:56.290 --> 23:58.281
3,020 meters.

23:58.290 --> 24:01.111
Pressure's
just below 4,400 psi.

24:01.120 --> 24:02.326
Roger that.

24:02.330 --> 24:04.491
Video feed is crystal clear.

24:04.500 --> 24:06.616
Lead the way, Captain.

24:13.790 --> 24:14.825
That way.

24:17.420 --> 24:19.411
[motors whining]

24:30.120 --> 24:31.417
[switches click]

24:33.040 --> 24:34.826
-[buzzes]
-What are you doing?

24:34.830 --> 24:36.411
[static, alarms beep]

24:36.420 --> 24:37.614
What just happened?

24:37.620 --> 24:39.281
We can't let them
see everything.

24:40.290 --> 24:41.416
They don't watch now?

24:41.420 --> 24:43.957
No, it's just us.

24:43.960 --> 24:45.700
Stop there.

24:46.880 --> 24:48.324
By that rock.

24:48.330 --> 24:49.615
Are you sure?

24:49.620 --> 24:50.871
Yes.

24:53.120 --> 24:55.873
[motors shutting down]

24:59.540 --> 25:01.280
[thud]

25:01.290 --> 25:02.325
[clicking]

25:05.790 --> 25:07.280
What do we do now?

25:07.290 --> 25:08.370
We wait.

25:14.500 --> 25:16.786
[vibration]

25:16.790 --> 25:19.167
Maddie, do you feel that?

25:19.170 --> 25:21.377
-[alarm beeping]
-A seismic tremor?

25:22.460 --> 25:23.324
No.

25:27.420 --> 25:30.207
-[loud vibrations]
-[alarm beeping]

25:31.540 --> 25:32.575
Ben!

25:41.500 --> 25:42.819
[alarm beeping]

25:42.830 --> 25:44.741
Research bridge to Nautac One.
Do you copy?

25:44.750 --> 25:46.377
Do you copy?

25:46.380 --> 25:48.371
[loud shaking]

25:51.420 --> 25:54.071
Research bridge to Nautac One.
Do you copy?

25:55.750 --> 25:56.819
Ben!

26:05.210 --> 26:07.576
[panï¬ng]

26:09.120 --> 26:11.111
[motors starting]

26:13.960 --> 26:15.496
We're okay. We're okay.

26:30.540 --> 26:33.498
[placid music]

26:34.500 --> 26:35.706
Incredible.

26:47.040 --> 26:48.450
What is this place?

26:48.460 --> 26:50.530
This is where Ryn began.

26:50.540 --> 26:51.746
Ryn, you were born here?

26:52.830 --> 26:53.819
Long ago.

26:55.380 --> 26:57.166
[Ben] This must be
their breeding ground.

26:57.170 --> 26:58.535
Where they come to mate.

26:58.540 --> 27:01.111
Yes. Mate again soon.

27:03.420 --> 27:04.660
Hey!

27:11.710 --> 27:13.416
You two know each other?

27:13.420 --> 27:14.455
Yes.

27:14.460 --> 27:16.826
She is family.

27:30.040 --> 27:31.746
Wait.

27:31.750 --> 27:33.320
Maddie, look.

27:38.830 --> 27:40.240
-[thud]
-Whoa!

27:40.250 --> 27:41.706
-[tails thumping]
-Whoa.

27:47.460 --> 27:48.916
-[alarm beeping]
-Ryn.

27:58.210 --> 28:00.701
We go.
To healing place.

28:00.710 --> 28:03.076
Yeah. Think
that's a good idea.

28:06.790 --> 28:08.200
That way.

28:19.120 --> 28:20.951
He was like Batman.

28:20.960 --> 28:22.245
One second
we're under attack.

28:22.250 --> 28:25.572
And next the second,
he swoops down from the slq

28:25.580 --> 28:27.036
and just cleans up shop.

28:27.040 --> 28:28.325
There was no swooping.

28:28.330 --> 28:30.207
Sounds like you were
luclq he was there.

28:30.210 --> 28:31.165
You could've
gotten really hurt.

28:31.170 --> 28:33.240
Oh, we got some punches in.

28:33.250 --> 28:35.878
Air shots don't count, babe.

28:35.880 --> 28:38.997
How about another plate of fries
for the man of the hour?

28:39.000 --> 28:40.035
Yes.

28:40.040 --> 28:42.372
You're paying
for that beer.

28:43.880 --> 28:46.166
What?!
I was just attacked!

28:46.170 --> 28:48.035
Babe!

28:48.040 --> 28:51.498
[rock ballad playing
in The Anchor]

28:51.500 --> 28:52.910
Why do you like it
here so much?

28:52.920 --> 28:54.876
I just don't get it.

28:54.880 --> 28:56.416
What's so great
about being on land?

28:56.420 --> 28:58.206
On land,

29:01.210 --> 29:02.450
I make choice.

29:05.880 --> 29:07.279
I get that.

29:07.290 --> 29:09.326
One more question.

29:09.330 --> 29:11.321
A song,
can you do that, too,

29:11.330 --> 29:13.878
or is it just,
like, a girl thing?

29:13.880 --> 29:15.279
I don't sing.

29:16.960 --> 29:19.281
But you can dance.

29:19.290 --> 29:21.952
[male singer] Every day
I'm feelin' good, yeah

29:28.960 --> 29:31.952
[sonar pinging]

29:38.290 --> 29:40.030
How far is this place?

29:40.040 --> 29:41.610
I don't know.

29:41.620 --> 29:43.702
-[crash]
-[Maddie groans]

29:43.710 --> 29:44.916
[scraping]

29:52.960 --> 29:56.248
[instruments buzzing]

30:01.960 --> 30:03.780
[powering down]

30:03.790 --> 30:05.371
-[alarm beeping]
-What's happening?

30:05.380 --> 30:07.200
[starter whines]

30:07.210 --> 30:08.245
It's not starting.

30:14.170 --> 30:15.660
[switch clicks, beeps]

30:15.670 --> 30:17.661
[rumbling]

30:20.210 --> 30:22.576
Ben,
are you doing this?

30:22.580 --> 30:24.377
[Ben] No.
We're getting pulled.

30:40.250 --> 30:42.878
[ethereal voices]

30:42.880 --> 30:44.199
Maddie, can you hear that?

30:44.210 --> 30:45.325
[Maddie] Yeah.

30:45.330 --> 30:47.207
I can feel it, too.

30:47.210 --> 30:50.327
[voices overlapping]

30:53.210 --> 30:54.450
[Maddie] It's everywhere.

30:58.000 --> 30:59.490
I'll start the recording.

31:04.210 --> 31:06.576
[voices intensifying]

31:08.460 --> 31:11.327
This sound, very old.

31:13.380 --> 31:15.109
Made from others like me.

31:15.120 --> 31:17.111
It's beautiful.

31:21.790 --> 31:23.701
[voices continuing]

31:23.710 --> 31:27.168
These must be the voices
of your ancestors, Ryn.

31:27.170 --> 31:29.411
What is "ancestors"?

31:29.420 --> 31:32.457
Your family...
from the past.

31:35.000 --> 31:38.037
Yes. Voices of family.

32:06.080 --> 32:07.570
[voicemail]
You've reached Ben Pownall.

32:07.580 --> 32:09.662
I'm not available.
Leave a mes--

32:09.670 --> 32:12.036
[rock music playing
in The Anchor]

32:12.040 --> 32:13.246
Look at that.

32:13.250 --> 32:14.456
This guy's killin' it.

32:14.460 --> 32:16.416
Four bull's-eyes in a row.

32:19.250 --> 32:20.820
My shift's over
in, like, an hour, man.

32:20.830 --> 32:22.536
What are we
gonna do with him?

32:22.540 --> 32:25.077
He's made it clear
he wants to stay.

32:25.080 --> 32:26.490
Fish wants to be free.

32:29.620 --> 32:30.609
Can you take him?

32:30.620 --> 32:31.666
Ha!

32:31.670 --> 32:34.457
Uh, no.
Janine would flip.

32:34.460 --> 32:36.701
Thanks to you, we have
a strict "no house guests" rule.

32:36.710 --> 32:37.950
He can't stay
at my mom's.

32:37.960 --> 32:39.530
That'd be weird.

32:39.540 --> 32:41.531
I think it's weird
you live with your mom.

32:41.540 --> 32:42.609
I'm serious, man.

32:44.460 --> 32:45.279
Where do we take him?

32:48.120 --> 32:49.246
-Helen's.
-Helen's.

32:58.170 --> 33:00.616
No communication
for almost four hours, Ben?

33:00.620 --> 33:02.372
Four hours?

33:02.380 --> 33:03.745
We didn't know
if you were lost or dead.

33:03.750 --> 33:06.162
We lost signal
after we hit the bottom.

33:06.170 --> 33:08.741
Some kind of technical
malfunction with the sonar.

33:08.750 --> 33:10.786
Do you understand
I'm the only one
in between you

33:10.790 --> 33:13.782
and this entire operation
being taken over?

33:13.790 --> 33:17.282
This pattern of you
not trusting me
is getting really old.

33:17.290 --> 33:18.746
What am I supposed
to tell my C.O.?

33:18.750 --> 33:22.959
Tell him that the mission
was a success.

33:22.960 --> 33:24.370
We got
what we were looking for.

33:26.460 --> 33:27.666
I'm on your side.

33:27.670 --> 33:29.069
I need you
to remember that.

33:29.080 --> 33:31.036
[crewman]
Move it back. Lock it up.

33:31.040 --> 33:32.166
Let's go.

33:42.000 --> 33:43.490
Ding dong.

33:44.540 --> 33:46.246
I come bearing gifts.

33:46.250 --> 33:48.878
Oh, I wish you
would've called first.

33:48.880 --> 33:50.450
Then it wouldn't be
a surprise, Silly.

33:52.420 --> 33:54.661
So, this is your shop?

33:54.670 --> 33:57.616
I'm thrilled I finally
get to see it in person.

33:57.620 --> 33:59.417
It was my mother's.

33:59.420 --> 34:02.617
We collected these relics
together for years.

34:02.620 --> 34:05.418
My mom and I
used to bake together

34:05.420 --> 34:07.320
every Tuesday after school.

34:07.330 --> 34:08.536
That's her recipe.

34:10.210 --> 34:12.201
_ We have a lot
in common, Helen.

34:13.330 --> 34:14.706
We value our roots.

34:16.380 --> 34:18.371
I suppose
you could say that.

34:18.380 --> 34:21.201
There aren't many
like us in the world.

34:21.210 --> 34:23.166
I think it's important
we try to trust each other.

34:25.040 --> 34:28.828
You're the one who had me
abducted in a parking lot.

34:28.830 --> 34:32.163
You, of all people, can
understand why we were afraid.

34:32.170 --> 34:34.377
Do you know
I have two boys?

34:35.540 --> 34:37.496
Max is eight,
Jake is six.

34:39.040 --> 34:40.746
If our secret ever got out,

34:40.750 --> 34:42.320
we'd be ripped apart.

34:42.330 --> 34:44.321
I hope you get that.

34:44.330 --> 34:48.744
I've been hiding
my entire life, Beth.

34:50.790 --> 34:51.916
I think I get it.

34:53.960 --> 34:56.997
What we need, you and I,
is a fresh start.

34:57.000 --> 34:59.571
-Some honesty.
-[laughs]

34:59.580 --> 35:02.822
Okay. Since
we're being honest,

35:02.830 --> 35:04.491
did your people
kill my father?

35:05.790 --> 35:07.166
What makes you ask that?

35:07.170 --> 35:09.821
I've been doing
some digging.

35:09.830 --> 35:11.536
I wouldn't even
have been born.

35:11.540 --> 35:15.954
I've heard stories
about your mother's
intermarriage,

35:15.960 --> 35:17.109
but that's all.

35:17.120 --> 35:20.499
So you knew
who I was all along?

35:20.500 --> 35:22.320
Who my parents were.

35:22.330 --> 35:26.243
Did you know I didn't even
get to meet my own father?

35:29.080 --> 35:31.321
So much for honesty.

35:33.170 --> 35:34.239
I should go.

35:34.250 --> 35:36.662
I think
that's a good idea.

35:36.670 --> 35:39.036
[ominous music]

36:12.830 --> 36:14.240
Hot off the press.

36:17.170 --> 36:18.455
Not dark anymore.

36:18.460 --> 36:20.951
That's right, Ryn.
Not dark.

36:22.580 --> 36:23.786
I don't believe it.

36:23.790 --> 36:25.667
So you're telling us
it worked?

36:25.670 --> 36:26.955
I'm saying
the echo chamber removed

36:26.960 --> 36:28.780
a considerable
amount of the damage.

36:28.790 --> 36:31.247
There are remnants
along the frontal lobe,

36:31.250 --> 36:32.706
mostly benign lesions.

36:32.710 --> 36:35.247
Whatever you were
exposed to down there,

36:36.880 --> 36:37.915
it helped.

36:39.250 --> 36:40.820
Oh, my God.

36:43.170 --> 36:44.660
You are okay?

36:44.670 --> 36:47.116
Yes, we're okay.

36:47.120 --> 36:49.202
We'll give
you three some privacy.

36:52.040 --> 36:53.826
I'm handing over
the recording to the techs.

36:53.830 --> 36:55.457
They'll start
their analysis in the morning.

36:55.460 --> 36:57.451
If this can help
keep you safe,

36:57.460 --> 36:59.371
maybe we can continue
helping your mom
with her treatment.

37:00.380 --> 37:02.280
Thanks, Nicole.

37:06.170 --> 37:07.319
[door opens]

37:09.210 --> 37:10.279
[door closes]

37:13.170 --> 37:15.161
[physical therapist]
A little more. Hold.

37:15.170 --> 37:17.707
One, two, three.

37:17.710 --> 37:19.371
Good.
Now back to center.

37:19.380 --> 37:22.952
Okay, hold. One, two, three.

37:22.960 --> 37:24.370
Good.

37:24.380 --> 37:26.280
Okay. I think
that's it for today, Ava.

37:26.290 --> 37:28.281
-Thank you.
-I'll see you Wednesday.

37:28.290 --> 37:29.609
Sounds good.

37:33.420 --> 37:35.786
Every day, it's
getting a little easier.

37:35.790 --> 37:37.781
This new treatment
has re-energized me.

37:37.790 --> 37:39.417
I feel better
than I did before.

37:39.420 --> 37:40.956
That's terrific, honey.

37:40.960 --> 37:42.029
What's that?

37:43.210 --> 37:45.326
I found these in the attic.

37:45.330 --> 37:48.993
They're letters exchanged
between my grandmother
and Helen's mother.

37:49.000 --> 37:52.117
What on earth did they
have to say to each other?

37:52.120 --> 37:55.374
Well, apparently Helen's mother
was in some kind of trouble.

37:55.380 --> 37:57.746
She was pregnant,
didn't know where to go.

37:57.750 --> 38:00.162
She sought out my grandmother,
looking for a place to hide.

38:01.420 --> 38:02.535
The cottage.

38:02.540 --> 38:05.077
They lived here?

38:08.210 --> 38:12.249
It's hard to imagine
the Pownalls and the Hawkins
ever being that close.

38:12.250 --> 38:14.286
Does it say
what she was hiding from?

38:15.290 --> 38:16.279
No.

38:23.040 --> 38:26.669
[female singer]
The winds are howlin'

38:26.670 --> 38:28.319
The trees are blowin'

38:28.330 --> 38:29.410
Just gotta
shut off the lights,

38:29.420 --> 38:30.910
then we'll get you
tucked in.

38:37.250 --> 38:39.377
Sorry, man. We're closed.

38:39.380 --> 38:40.415
Calvin?

38:41.250 --> 38:44.287
Ian Sutton, KFGT News.

38:44.290 --> 38:46.281
You reached out to me
a few weeks ago.

38:46.290 --> 38:48.326
Yeah. I remember.

38:48.330 --> 38:50.116
Yeah, look, I know
this is out of the blue,

38:50.120 --> 38:52.418
but I was hoping I could
take a look at that, uh--

38:52.420 --> 38:53.284
the video you showed me.

38:53.290 --> 38:54.575
The one from the boat?

38:54.580 --> 38:56.241
What, you believe me now?

38:56.250 --> 38:59.117
I'm following up on a lead.

38:59.120 --> 39:00.951
I think I'm ready to hear
what you have to say about...

39:03.290 --> 39:04.416
you know.

39:08.250 --> 39:09.990
Turns_out
you were right, bro.

39:10.000 --> 39:11.319
It was just a sea lion.

39:11.330 --> 39:14.572
[dramatic music]

39:29.040 --> 39:32.032
[somber music]

39:37.790 --> 39:39.451
[Helen] I know.

39:39.460 --> 39:40.666
I miss him, too.

39:46.380 --> 39:50.077
[adventure movie music on TV]

39:55.290 --> 39:56.575
All right.

40:00.420 --> 40:02.035
[man in movie] Throw!

40:02.040 --> 40:03.450
[man screams]

40:05.960 --> 40:07.109
It's got me!

40:08.120 --> 40:09.917
Watch on the bow!

40:13.290 --> 40:14.530
[knock on door]

40:20.170 --> 40:22.070
Great timing.
I was just about
to order dinner.

40:22.080 --> 40:24.287
Good. I am starving.

40:24.290 --> 40:26.531
Hey, whoa! Not so fast,
not so fast. Hey.

40:26.540 --> 40:28.531
Don't I get a kiss? Huh?

40:30.380 --> 40:31.449
How was your day?

40:33.420 --> 40:35.320
Nothing to report.
How was yours?

40:36.380 --> 40:37.369
Just the same.

40:37.380 --> 40:38.449
Uh, Chinese sound good?

40:38.460 --> 40:40.701
-Yeah, sounds perfect.
-'Kay.

40:40.710 --> 40:43.110
Uh, I'm gonna hop
in the shower real quick,
if that's cool?

40:43.120 --> 40:44.530
Roger that.

40:48.290 --> 40:50.417
[rustling]

40:50.420 --> 40:51.876
[suspenseful music]

40:54.120 --> 40:56.076
[shower running]

40:58.290 --> 41:00.702
[Xander whistling]

41:04.380 --> 41:06.871
[line ringing]

41:06.880 --> 41:08.609
Yeah, I'd like
to place an order.

41:09.880 --> 41:10.869
Delivery.

41:14.210 --> 41:16.030
Sure, I can hold.

41:16.040 --> 41:18.827
[female singer]
This is warfare

41:21.920 --> 41:24.992
This is warfare

41:27.830 --> 41:30.879
This is warfare

41:34.040 --> 41:36.110
We won't stop

41:37.710 --> 41:41.498
[music playing]
